HEADWORD: Conventicling
<hw>Con*ven"ti*cling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Belonging or
going to, or resembling, a conventicle.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Conventicling</qex> schools . . . set up and taught secretly
by fanatics.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convention</ent>⟦br⟧
